            . I lodge at <placeName id="t18221204-164-crimeloc842">the Falstaff, public-house, Old-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18221204-164-crimeloc842" type="placeName" value="the Falstaff, public-house, Old-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18221204-164-crimeloc842" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-164-off840 t18221204-164-crimeloc842"></join> - the prisoner lodged in the same room. On the 17th of November, I laid my watch on the bed about two o'clock in the afternoon - I went out, and returned between nine and ten o'clock; it was then gone -<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182212040061"></xptr>the prisoner was at home. Next morning I followed him to a pawnbroker's in St. John-street, and when he came out I went in, and found it there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-164-person1410">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HOLROYD
               <interp inst="t18221204-164-person1410" type="surname" value="HOLROYD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-164-person1410" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-164-person1410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I sleep in the same room as the prisoner and witness. I went up stairs in the afternoon, and saw the prisoner lying across the bed intoxicated; he awoke, undressed, and got into bed. I went down and left him there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-164-person1411">
                  JAMES 
                  WOOD
               <interp inst="t18221204-164-person1411" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
